@node disclaimer "StUC v1.09 (Disclaimer)"
I  nor  any other member of Area 51 may be held responsible for the (mis)use
of this program.  The program is released "as-is".  If you end up destroying
the world then its your fault.
@endnode
@node distribution "StUC v1.09 (Distribution)"
If  you decide to spread @{i}StUC @{ui}(which I hope you will!) then the files listed
below @{b}MUST@{ub} be distributed in the same archive:
	File_ID.diz		ID file for archives
	L/WBStart-Handler
	StUC.info		Drawer icon for Workbench
	StUC/StUC		Main executable file
	StUC/StUC.info		Workbench icon
	StUC/StUC.gde		This file
	StUC/StUC.gde.info	Workbench icon
None of the above files may be modified in any way or disassembled.  I'm NOT
offering the source code out any more so please don't write asking for it as
you'll  get  a  flat refusal!  But if you want to trade E source code then I
suppose I can be persuaded!

StUC  may  not  be disassembled or spread in part but only in whole.

StUC  IS  DISTRIBUTED UNDER POSTCARD-WARE.  IF YOU LIKE AND/OR USE IT THEN A
POSTCARD WOULD BE APPRECIATED.  I DON'T WANT CASH OR ANYTHING ELSE SO PLEASE
DON'T SEND ME ANY.
@endnode
